        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1961-04-18T17:12:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1961-04-18T17:12:00-05:00" n="127"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d127">
                <head>127. Telegram From the Commander of Special Task Group 81.8 (<persName
                        corresp="#p_CRAJE1" type="from">Clark</persName>) to the Commander in Chief,
                    Atlantic (<persName corresp="#p_DARL1" type="to">Dennison</persName>)<note n="0"
                        type="source" xml:id="d127fn0">Source: Naval Historical Center, Area Files,
                        Bumpy Road Materials. Top Secret; Emergency. Repeated to <gloss
                            target="#t_JCS1">JCS</gloss>, <gloss target="#t_COMCARIBSEAFRON1"
                            >COMCARIBSEAFRON</gloss>, <gloss target="#t_COMKWESTFOR1"
                            >COMKWESTFOR</gloss>, and COMNAVBASE <gloss target="#t_GTMO1"
                            >GTMO</gloss>.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <gloss target="#t_USS1">USS</gloss> Essex, Caribbean</placeName>, <date
                            calendar="gregorian" when="1961-04-18T17:12:00">April 18, 1961, 5:12
                            p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>182212Z. Exclusive for <persName corresp="#p_DARL1">Dennison</persName>,
                        <persName corresp="#p_GMGDW1">Gray</persName>, <persName corresp="#p_SBK1"
                        >Smith</persName>, OʼDonnell and McElroy from <persName corresp="#p_CRAJE1"
                        >Clark</persName>. Bumpy Road. Eyeball <gloss target="#t_RECCO1"
                        >recco</gloss> report over area about 2120Z.<note n="1" xml:id="d127fn1"
                        >4:20 p.m.</note>
                </p>
                <list>
                    <label>1.</label>
                    <item>Convoy of large <persName corresp="#p_CRF1">Castro</persName> tanks (10 to
                        14) with trucks and lorries on road from Gallinas extending to point about
                        three miles south moving south and east. Only a few troops seen with convoy.
                        No others sighted.</item>
                    <label>2.</label>
                    <item>
                        <gloss target="#t_CEF1">CEF</gloss> tanks and trucks burned out alongside
                        road near La Seiba. No sign of <gloss target="#t_CEF1">CEF</gloss>
                        troops.</item>
                    <label>3.</label>
                    <item>No air activity seen. No sign of artillery or infantry action.</item>
                    <label>4.</label>
                    <item>Own evaluation Red Beach wiped out. Attacks on other beaches thus far have
                        been almost entirely by air.</item>
                </list>
            </div>
        </body>
